Here's the complete migration plan for your project. I identified **6 breaking changes** by analyzing your code against MSTest 4.x:

---

### 1. Upgrade TFM: `net6.0` → `net8.0`
MSTest 4.x dropped support for `net6.0` (which is also EOL). Minimum is `net8.0`.

### 2. Upgrade project to MSTest SDK (or meta-package)
Replace individual package references with the `MSTest.Sdk` or `MSTest` meta-package:
```xml
<!-- Option A: MSTest SDK (recommended) -->
<Project Sdk="MSTest.Sdk/4.2.3">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
  </PropertyGroup>
</Project>
```
```xml
<!-- Option B: MSTest meta-package -->
<PackageReference Include="MSTest" Version="4.2.3" />
<!-- Remove MSTest.TestFramework, MSTest.TestAdapter, Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk -->
```

### 3. Replace `[ExpectedException]` → `Assert.ThrowsExactly`
**Removed in v4.** Replace:
```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_BadInput_Throws()
{
    throw new ArgumentException("bad");
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_BadInput_Throws()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentException>(() => throw new ArgumentException("bad"));
}
```

### 4. Remove `ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass`
**Removed in v4** — `EndOfClass` is now the default. Change:
```csharp
// Before
[ClassCleanup(ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass)]
// After
[ClassCleanup]
```

### 5. Custom `TestMethodAttribute`: propagate caller info (MSTEST0057)
MSTest 4 requires source info propagation:
```csharp
// Before
public sealed class LoggingTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    // implicit parameterless ctor
}

// After
public sealed class LoggingTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public LoggingTestMethodAttribute(
        [CallerFilePath] string callerFilePath = "",
        [CallerLineNumber] int callerLineNumber = -1)
        : base(callerFilePath, callerLineNumber) { }
}
```

### 6. Replace Assert format parameters → string interpolation (MSTEST0053)
**Removed in v4.** The `message + params` overloads no longer exist:
```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreEqual(1, 1, "Expected {0}", 1);
// After
Assert.AreEqual(1, 1, $"Expected {1}");
```

---

### Summary of all changes needed

| Area | Issue | Action |
|------|-------|--------|
| TFM | `net6.0` unsupported | → `net8.0` |
| Packages | Separate packages | → `MSTest.Sdk` or `MSTest` meta-package |
| `[ExpectedException]` | Removed | → `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` | Removed | → bare `[ClassCleanup]` |
| Custom `TestMethodAttribute` | Missing caller info | → Add `CallerFilePath`/`CallerLineNumber` ctor |
| Assert format params | Removed | → String interpolation |

Want me to implement these changes?
